   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="letter">
            <pb n="1" facs="uoedh_hl_h.1365_1.jpg"/>

            <opener>
               <address>
                  <addrLine>The Old Vicarage: Dorchester.</addrLine>

               </address>
               <dateline>
                  <date when="1926-06-01">1<hi rend="superscript">st</hi> June 1926</date>
               </dateline>



               <salute>Dear Mr Hardy:</salute>
            </opener>

            <p>I cannot find in <placeName ref="#pl:Dorchester">Dorchester</placeName> a card which
               I like well enough to send you for your Birthday, so please accept a plain
               paper-and-ink greeting! I will make it brief because I know you will have so
               many.</p>

            <p>This is my third year with you, and dear <persName ref="#ps:FlorenceHardy">Mrs
                  Hardy</persName>, and Wessie, and I can frame no better wish than that the years
               ahead will make you as happy as my three years at <placeName ref="#pl:MaxGate">Max
                  Gate</placeName> have made me.</p>

            <p>Thank you for all your kindness!</p>


            <closer>
               <salute>Yours sincerely</salute>
               <signed>
                  <hi rend="underline">May O'Rourke</hi>
               </signed>
            </closer>
            <pb n="2" facs="uoedh_hl_h.1365_2.jpg"/>

            <!-- No text on this page other than H. number -->

         </div>
